// Off-screen image rendering
// Renders scene content to raw pixel bytes (PNG/JPG/WEBP) by creating a CanvasKit off-screen surface, drawing the scene onto it, and encoding the result.
// synced: 2026-03-26T00:00:00Z

FUNCTION computeContentBounds(graph, nodeIds) -> bounds | null [2026-03-26]
  CALLS: getNode, getAbsolutePosition (scene-graph)
  Iterates visible nodes and accumulates their absolute bounding boxes to find the overall min/max extent. Returns null if no visible nodes are found.

---

FUNCTION ckImageFormat(ck, format) -> CanvasKit.ImageFormat [2026-03-26]
  Maps an ExportFormat string ('PNG', 'JPG', 'WEBP') to the corresponding CanvasKit ImageFormat enum value.

---

FUNCTION renderToSurface(ck, renderer, graph, pageId, width, height, format, quality, setup) -> Uint8Array | null [2026-03-26]
  CALLS: renderSceneToCanvas (renderer)
  Creates a CanvasKit off-screen surface of the given dimensions, runs the setup callback to configure the canvas transform, renders the scene, snapshots the image, encodes it, and cleans up. Returns null if surface creation fails.

---

FUNCTION renderNodesToImage(ck, renderer, graph, pageId, nodeIds, options) -> Uint8Array | null [2026-03-26] EXPORT
  CALLS: computeContentBounds (render-image), renderToSurface (render-image)
  Computes the bounding box of the given nodes, scales to pixel dimensions, sets up a clear + scale + translate transform, and delegates to renderToSurface. Returns null if bounds are empty.

---

FUNCTION renderThumbnail(ck, renderer, graph, pageId, width, height) -> Uint8Array | null [2026-03-26] EXPORT
  CALLS: computeContentBounds (render-image), renderToSurface (render-image)
  Renders a centered, fit-scaled thumbnail of all page children onto a background-filled PNG surface of fixed dimensions.
